    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Numeric</title>
        <introduction>
          <p>For the following exercises, evaluate the function <m>f</m> at the values <m>f(-2),f(-1),f(0),f(1),</m> and <m>f(2).</m>
          </p>
        </introduction>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-Y2KfAA1rvn-parts" original="PRECALC/modules/m49301/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>f(x)=4-2x</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>f(x)=8-3x</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>f(x)=8x^{2}-7x+3</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>f(x)=3+\sqrt{x+3}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>f(x)=\frac{x-2}{x+3}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>f(x)=3^{x}</m>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>f(-2)=14; &amp; f(-1)=11; &amp; f(0)=8; &amp; f(1)=5; &amp; f(2)=2</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>f(-2)=4; &amp; f(-1)=4.414; &amp; f(0)=4.732; &amp; f(1)=5; &amp; f(2)=5.236</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>f(-2)=\frac{1}{9}; &amp; f(-1)=\frac{1}{3}; &amp; f(0)=1; &amp; f(1)=3; &amp; f(2)=9</m>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
  
    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Numeric</title>
