    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Graphical</title>
        <introduction>
          <p>For the following exercises, determine whether the graph of the function provided is a graph of a polynomial function. If so, determine the number of turning points and the least possible degree for the function.</p>
        </introduction>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-yBm8RMeWdW" original="PRECALC/modules/m49346/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
            <image xml:id="PRECALC-pSM17OLC5r" original="PRECALC/modules/m49346/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0" source="PRECALC/CNX_Precalc_Figure_03_03_209.jpg" width="80%">
              <description>
                               Graph of an odd-degree polynomial.
                           </description>
            </image>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <p>Yes. Number of turning points is 2. Least possible degree is 3.</p>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-XsVBdydCYL" original="PRECALC/modules/m49346/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
