      </exercisegroup>
  
    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Algebraic</title>
        <introduction>
          <p>For the following exercises, describe the local and end behavior of the functions.</p>
        </introduction>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-R7EJWrISq7-parts" original="PRECALC/modules/m49351/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>f(x)=\frac{x}{2x+1}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>f(x)=\frac{2x}{x-6}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>f(x)=\frac{-2x}{x-6}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>f(x)=\frac{x^{2}-4x+3}{x^{2}-4x-5}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>f(x)=\frac{2x^{2}-32}{6x^{2}+13x-5}</m>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>Local behavior: <m>x \to -\frac{1}{2}^{+},f(x) \to -∞,x \to -\frac{1}{2}^{-},f(x) \to ∞</m>
              </li>
              <p>End behavior: <m>x \to ±∞,f(x) \to \frac{1}{2}</m>
              </p>
              <li/>
              <li>Local behavior: <m>x \to 6^{+},f(x) \to -∞,x \to 6^{-},f(x) \to ∞,</m> End behavior: <m>x \to ±∞,f(x) \to -2</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>Local behavior: <m>x \to \frac{1}{3}^{+},f(x) \to –∞,x \to \frac{1}{3}^{-},</m>
                <m>f(x) \to ∞,x \to -\frac{5}{2}^{-},f(x) \to –∞,x \to -\frac{5}{2}^{+}</m>, <m>f(x) \to ∞</m>
              </li>
              <p>End behavior: <m>x \to ±∞,</m>
                <m>f(x) \to \frac{1}{3}</m>
              </p>
            </ol>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
  
    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Algebraic</title>
